I"‚<h1 id="generate-ctags-for-all-bundled-gems-in-a-ruby-project">Generate ctags for all bundled gems in a ruby project</h1>

<p>You can make bundler show the locations for the gems in the gemfile with</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bundle show --paths</code></p>

<p>If you pipe this list into ctags, it will generate tags for all gems specified in the gemfile.</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">bundle show --paths | xargs ctags -R</code></p>

<p>To index the tags and append the tags for your project run</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">ctags -R -a *</code></p>
:ET